<h2 class="popup-title">GP Services</h2>
<p class="popup-content">We offer adult only private doctor services for the diagnosis and treatment of minor illness at many of our health centres throughout the UK, giving you access to doctors without having to wait for an appointment.
</p>
<p class="popup-content">Youâ€™ll also get sufficient time with a doctor and not feel rushed so you can properly discuss your health concerns or illness.  The amount of time you need with the doctor will depend on how many concerns of illnesses you need to discuss and the complexity.  Please refer to the â€˜how long do I needâ€™ link for further information.
</p>
<p class="popup-content">Our doctors offer a range of services, from advice on minor illnesses to women and menâ€™s health. If you require further investigations we can organise blood tests or scans at an additional cost. Private consultant referrals and private prescription notes are supplied at no extra cost.</p>
<p>Please be aware that our service cannot provide all the services available from your NHS doctor. In particular we are unable to Â manage acute medical, surgical and psychiatric emergencies including treating cuts and wounds, prescribe controlled drugs including tranquillisers and night sedation, or initiate anti-depressant medication, ear wax syringing and sexual health screening.
</p>
<p class="popup-content">We offer two appointment slots, our standard is 30 minutes but we also offer a shorter appointment for 15 minutes. If you believe you need a longer appointment please contact our booking team on 0333 305 7965. Lines are open 8am to 6pm Monday to Friday, weâ€™re closed on weekends. We may record or monitor our calls.</p>
<p><strong><em>Please note: in order to keep customers and staff safe, we are unable to see customers who are required to self-isolate or quarantine under UK government guidelines. This includes: customers with symptoms of COVID-19 in the 7 days prior to their appointment; customers who have had contact with a potential/confirmed case (including household members) of COVID-19 in the 14 days prior to their appointment; and customers who have returned from a country requiring a quarantine period in the 14 days prior to their appointment.</em></strong></p>
